Package org.hibernate.boot.registry.internal

Class BootstrapServiceRegistryImpl

java.lang.Object
org.hibernate.boot.registry.internal.BootstrapServiceRegistryImpl
All Implemented Interfaces:
AutoCloseable, BootstrapServiceRegistry, ServiceRegistry, ServiceBinding.ServiceLifecycleOwner, ServiceRegistryImplementor
public class BootstrapServiceRegistryImpl extends Object implements ServiceRegistryImplementor, BootstrapServiceRegistry, ServiceBinding.ServiceLifecycleOwner
ServiceRegistry implementation containing specialized "bootstrap" services, specifically:
  • ClassLoaderService
  • IntegratorService
  • StrategySelector

  • Method Details

    • getService

      public <R extends Service> @Nullable R getService(Class<R> serviceRole)
      Description copied from interface: ServiceRegistry
      Retrieve a service by role, returning null if there is no such service. If service is not found, but a ServiceInitiator is registered for this service role, the service will be initialized and returned. Most of the time, use of ServiceRegistry.requireService(Class) is preferred, being much less likely to cause a NullPointerException in the client.
      Specified by:
      getService in interface ServiceRegistry
      Type Parameters:
      R - The service role type
      Parameters:
      serviceRole - The service role
      Returns:
      The requested service or null if the service was not found.
